<figure class='article-image'><img alt="Appwtclck" class="microcontent" data-fragment="lead-image" data-image="http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE1LzA4LzAxLzZjL2FwcHd0Y2xjay5mNmVmNy5qcGcKcAl0aHVtYgk5NTB4NTM0IwplCWpwZw/0f553711/aa2/appwtclck.jpg" data-micro="1" data-url="null" src="http://rack.0.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE1LzA4LzAxLzZjL2FwcHd0Y2xjay5mNmVmNy5qcGcKcAl0aHVtYgk5NTB4NTM0IwplCWpwZw/0f553711/aa2/appwtclck.jpg" /><div class="image-credit">Image: Lynne Cameron/Associated Press</div></figure>

<div class="article-info"><a class="byline" href="/people/adario-strange/"><img alt="Nycmsh" class="author_image" src="http://rack.3.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDEzLzA5LzA5LzY1L255Y21zaC41YjdjOS5qcGcKcAl0aHVtYgk5MHg5MCMKZQlqcGc/ef31383c/d7f/nycmsh.jpg" /><div class="author_and_date"><span class="author_name">By Adario Strange</span><time datetime="Sat, 01 Aug 2015 23:14:17 +0000">2015-08-01 23:14:17 UTC</time></div></a></div>

</header>
<section class='article-content'>

<p>Owners of an Apple Watch just got another tool to make life easier: a digital door key on their wrists. </p>
<p>The functionality comes via the August Smart Lock thanks to an update of the company's iPhone app that allows you to swipe and tap your Apple Watch to open an <a href="http://mashable.com/category/august-smart-lock/">August Smart Lock</a>-equipped door. </p>
<div class="see-also"><p>See also: <a href="http://mashable.com/2015/07/23/apple-pulls-nest-thermostat-from-stores/" data-crackerjax="#post-slider">Apple yanks Google's Nest smart thermostat from website and retail stores</a></p></div>
<figure class="image"><p><img data-credit-link="" data-credit-name="August Smart Lock " data-credit-label="" data-credit-provider="Custom type" data-caption="" title="august smart lock apple watch app" src="http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE1LzA4LzAxLzkxL2F1Z3NwcHd0Y2guYmFhNTMuanBnCnAJdGh1bWIJMTIwMHg5NjAwPg/04798ad9/d57/augsppwtch.jpg" alt="august smart lock apple watch app" class="" data-width="950" data-fragment="m!377c" data-image="http://rack.1.mshcdn.com/media/ZgkyMDE1LzA4LzAxLzkxL2F1Z3NwcHd0Y2guYmFhNTMuanBnCnAJdGh1bWIJMTIwMHg5NjAwPg/04798ad9/d57/augsppwtch.jpg" data-micro="1"></p>
<div class="image-credit"><p>Image:  August Smart Lock </p></div></figure><p>Although the <a href="http://mashable.com/category/apple-watch/">Apple Watch</a> functionality is essentially just a porting of August's iPhone app to your wrist, it immediately makes the notion of using the smart door lock a lot more practical and faster than digging your iPhone out to open a door. </p>
<p>Back in April, Starwood hotels made news when it <a href="http://mashable.com/2015/05/15/starwood-technology/" data-crackerjax="#post-slider">showed off an app</a> that allows its guests to use the Apple Watch to open hotel room doors in roughly 100 of its locations (which includes the W Hotel). But August's solution brings the Apple Watch-powered smart home dynamic to the mainstream.  </p>
<blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-version="4" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"><div style="padding:8px;">
<div style=" background:#F8F8F8; line-height:0; margin-top:40px; padding:50% 0; text-align:center; width:100%;"><div style=" background:url(data:image/png;base64,); display:block; height:44px; margin:0 auto -44px; position:relative; top:-22px; width:44px;"></div></div>
<p style=" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px; margin-bottom:0; margin-top:8px; overflow:hidden; padding:8px 0 7px; text-align:center; text-overflow:ellipsis; white-space:nowrap;"><a href="https://instagram.com/p/2byV0sDVGB/" style=" color:#c9c8cd; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:normal; line-height:17px; text-decoration:none;" target="_blank">A video posted by Zach Honig (@zachhonig)</a> on <time style=" font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; line-height:17px;" datetime="2015-05-08T20:21:41+00:00">May 8, 2015 at 1:21pm PDT</time></p>
</div></blockquote>
<script async defer src="//platform.instagram.com/en_US/embeds.js"></script><p>In addition to the lock and unlock features, the Apple Watch app also instantly sends you a notification when someone unlocks your door. A silent, Taptic Engine tap on your wrist to alert you to someone entering your home is arguably a lot more seamless than constantly looking for such notifications on your iPhone screen. </p>
<p>The August Smart Lock costs $250 and <a href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/august-smart-lock/id648730592?ls=1&amp;mt=8" target="_blank">you can download</a> the Apple Watch app for free from Apple's App Store. </p>
<p><em>Have something to add to this story? Share it in the comments.</em></p>



</section>
